the last time new mexico tinkered with its 
election system democrat bruce king in 1970 became the states 
first governor in more than 50 years to be elected to a fouryear 
term 
twenty years later new mexico again has changed the rules and 
king is among eight candidates hoping to become the states first 
governor to be eligible to serve two consecutive fouryear terms 
the chance to serve eight straight years has attracted four 
democrats and four republicans to the june 5 gubernatorial 
primaries the largest field in 16 years republican gov garrey 
carruthers was not eligible to run 
i thought it would be a real opportunity to have an agenda and 
