very bad for this state because we havent developed any 
continuity in government 
new mexicos governors were limited to two consecutive twoyear 
terms until 1970 for the next 20 years they were elected to 
fouryear terms but incumbents could not seek reelection 
this years democratic primary has been largely a battle between 
bardacke and king a 66yearold rancher and businessman who offers 
voters the experience he gained in eight years as governor 
four gop contenders meanwhile are hoping to become the first 
republican governor to succeed a gop incumbent since 1920 
king who served longer than anyone else in the states history 
