the sweeping legislation is the first strengthening of federal 
clean air laws in 13 years and imposes new curbs on acid rain 
pollution industrial toxic releases and smogcausing emissions 
from industry and automobiles it is expected to cost more than 21 
billion a year when fully implemented 
the senate approved a similar measure in april 
the house began debate on the clean air bill monday while 
closeddoor talks continued in an effort to work out compromises on 
some of more than a halfdozen proposed amendments 
