nearly all of el salvadors top military 
commanders have been in charge of units linked to human rights 
abuses according to a study released on the eve of a house battle 
over cutting us military aid 
fourteen of the countrys 15 senior military officials have 
commanded units documented to have killed civilians tortured 
prisoners kidnapped citizens or covered up such abuses found a 
study by the arms control and foreign policy caucus 
the report did not seek to establish direct participation in 
human rights crimes by the officers who include chief of staff 
col rene emilio ponce but it said the groups rise to power at 
least illustrates a striking lack of accountability in the 
countrys military 
