anybody can roll around the capital in a 
darkwindowed limousine but what it costs depends on who you are 
a teenager on the way to the prom can end up paying six times more 
than an aging big shot 
thats age discrimination say three area high school students 
who filed complaints with local government consumer officials 
teenagers are charged the most even though limousine service 
managers say theyre often the best behaved they dont drink and 
they tip well because its not their money 
adults pay roughly 60 an hour for a chauffeurdriven limousine 
and the customer determines how long the rental will last teenaged 
promgoers pay a lump sum of about 400 for a minimum of six hours 
kearney c francis 16 said she called 30 area limousine 
services wanting a chauffeur to drive her and her friends to a 
restaurant then around the city for a quick tour and then to the 
prom where they would find their own way home all in all a 
threehour job 
