century in the 1950s egypt and syria joined as the united arab 
republic but the merger collapsed after three years because of 
internal squabbling 
the new state binds 11 million people 9 million from the north 
and 2 million from the south 
south yemen became the arab worlds only avowedly marxist state 
after it gained independence from britain in 1971 but it began to 
reform as democratic changes swept through the soviet union and 
eastern europe 
the two yemens are poor and undeveloped labor unrest in south 
