here are some facts and figures on the republic of yemen which 
was created tuesday by the merger of north yemen and south yemen 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the land yemen spans 203645 square miles on the southwestern 
edge of the arabian peninsula and has borders with saudi arabia and 
oman the country controls the bab almandab strait the strategic 
gateway to the red sea the north is mainly mountainous with a 
narow coastal strip on the red sea the south has a sandy coastline 
along the gulf of aden backed by barren mountains 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the people yemen has 11 million people they are mainly 
tribal and the main religion is sunni islam a few hundred jews 
live in the north and there are small communities of christians 
and hindus in the south 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the economy yemen is among the poorest nations in the world 
but newly discovered oil reserves could change that unofficial 
estimates say the reserves could amount to as much as 2 billion 
barrels 
the south depended heavily on aid from the soviet bloc but the 
collapse of communism in eastern europe apparently prompted the 
south to drop its marxist policies and agreed to a merger the 
major activities in the south are the refinery of aden the citys 
port and fishing 
money from millions of yemenis working outside their country 
mainly in the oilrich gulf and from foreign aid helped prop up 
the economy of the conservative prowestern north for years 
farming is the main activity in the region and crops include 
wheat sorghum coffee tobacco and cotton 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
history by merging the north and south regained their former 
status as part of ancient arabia felix and the kingdom of sheba 
that lasted for 800 years until the 2nd century bc 
for the next 800 years it was ruled by the himyarites one of 
the earliest arab tribes then by ethiopians and persians until 
islam arrived in the 7th century 
in 1517 south yemen became part of the ottoman empire britain 
seized aden in 1839 and the surrounding territory later became a 
british protectorate 
aden won independence in 1967 after a terrorist campaign and 
south yemen became the arab worlds only selfproclaimed marxist 
state 
the northern country the yemen arab republic was established 
in 1962 after an egyptianbacked revolution ousted the saudi 
arabianbacked imam 
