that the navys publicly stated goal for 1990 is 547 ships 
including 14 aircraft carriers four battleships and 34 ballistic 
missile submarines 
but recent published reports said civilian and military leaders 
drafted spending plans that suggest 488 ships including 12 
aircraft carriers 
