affairs subcommittee on international operations recently traveled 
to kuwait 
he told a congressional panel the compound is a ripe target 
for terrorist activities and that he would have had a clear shot 
at the no 2 embassy official from his hotel room 
kuwait is significant to the united states on several counts 
and the embassys job reflects that its staff of 80 people about 
half of them military is the secondlargest us diplomatic 
mission in the persian gulf region after riyadh saudi arabia 
kuwait is involved in an issue of key importance to the united 
states that of western hostages in lebanon the release of 15 
proiranian convicts held in kuwaiti jails is one of the 
proiranian kidnappers demands 
