china has bought an additional 399350 metric 
tons of us wheat under a price subsidy program the agriculture 
department said tuesday 
christopher e goldthwaite acting general sales manager for the 
departments foreign agricultural service said seven private 
exporting companies made the deals under the departments export 
enhancement program or eep 
delivery of the wheat is scheduled for july and august he said 
the sales were part of 2 million tons authorized china under eep 
on may 2 previous allocations had been exhausted except for 5050 
tons 
a metric ton is about 2205 pounds and is equal to 367 bushels 
of wheat the latest sales would be about 147 million bushels at 
current prices estimated by usda at around 336 per bushel the 
wheat would have a farm value of around 49 million 
under eep arrangements private exporters can sell us 
commodities at reduced prices to meet foreign competition in 
selected overseas markets and then collect free government 
surpluses of grain or other commodities as bonuses or subsidies 
goldthwaite said the latest subsidies averaged 1120 per ton 
or about 31 cents per bushel 
the subsidized sales were handled by louis dreyfus corp 
155000 tons alfred c toepfer international inc 50000 
tradigrain inc 49750 j aron and co 45000 continental grain 
co 39600 bunge corp 30000 and ferruzzi usa inc 30000 
