begin swapping proposals about cutting the deficit for the next 
fiscal year which begins oct 1 the opening discussions have 
focused on technical issues 
the goal of the talks is to find ways to reduce the 1991 
shortfall to 64 billion the target set by the grammrudman 
deficitreduction law 
if the budget gap exceeds that amount by 10 billion the law 
triggers whatever spending cuts are necessary to lower the gap to 
64 billion 
