said the united states welcomed the union and will review its 
listing of south yemen as a country that supports terrorism 
we welcome this declaration as a measure that could improve 
stability and security in the region she told reporters 
obviously it has not changed that south yemen is on the terrorist 
list in the hours that this has taken place 
saleh met with president bush at the white house last january 
and the united states resumed diplomatic relations with south yemen 
last april 30 after a break of nearly 21 years 
the merger was approved monday by the parliaments of the former 
countries it was pushed through several days earlier than planned 
so the yemens could attend the arab summit as one nation 
the new nation has 11 million people 9 million from the north 
and 2 million from the south and is one of the poorest countries 
in the world 
south yemen became the arab worlds only marxist state after it 
gained independence from britain in 1967 
although it received aid from the soviet union the souths 
economy had languished for 20 years and there had been widespread 
labor unrest in recent months some arab diplomatic sources said 
the south endorsed unity mainly because of the democratic reforms 
sweeping eastern europe 
scores of cuban and east german military experts are said to 
have left the south in recent months a friendship pact entitles 
the soviets to maintain as many as 18000 troops in yemen but the 
extent of their deployment is unknown 
sana will be the capital of the new state and aden the main 
commercial center sana was formerly the capital of the north and 
aden the capital of the south 
saleh 48 was elected president of the fiveman presidential 
council that will rule yemen 
ali salem albeidh the secretarygeneral of the socialist party 
that had ruled the south was elected vicepresident 
the three others on the presidential council are salem saleh 
mohammed albeidhs deputy abdulaziz alarashi a lawmaker from 
the north and abdulaziz abdulghani the former prime minister of 
the north 
