remainder of the fiveyear terms for the legislatures of the former 
nations 
it was the second such union between two arab states in this 
century egypt and syria joined for three years as the united arab 
republic but the merger collapsed in 1961 with damascus accusing 
cairo of betrayal and of wrecking its economy 
