broadcasting 
there is no political problem with western programs he told 
reporters at the media summit a conference of broadcast 
specialists and policy makers from europe and the united states 
as far as european and us programs are concerned we are 
working very hard to receive them in the soviet union he said 
but because of technical difficulties i do not think we will 
have it on a large scale in the near future 
he said soviets are bored of watching the often televised 
political debates and are hungry for european and american movies 
television shows music and youth programs 
in these days of glasnost and perestroika our television 
uses most of its time for political items its too much he 
