fading movie star was directed by spanish filmmaker pedro 
almodovar the director also made the offbeat comedy women on the 
verge of a nervous breakdown which in 1989 received an academy 
award nomination for best foreign film 
the mpaa doesnt publicly announce a reason for giving the 
rating which means no one under 17 is permitted to see the movie 
but a passionate lovemaking scene is believed the reason 
on april 24 miramax appealed the decision to the mpaas rating 
appeals board which upheld the rating on a 66 vote the suit 
alleges the decision was arbitrary and capricious 
in 1968 the mpaa and the national association of theater owners 
devised the voluntary system under which filmmakers submit their 
movies to be rated 
filmmakers have the option of releasing a film unrated and 
that was done with tie me up tie me down 
amanda marashinky a publicist at miramax noted that many 
theaters wont show xrated or unrated pictures and that many 
newspapers wont accept advertising for them 
i think a lot of people have brought up the fact that it isnt 
really voluntary marashinsky said 
in the past few months wild orchid henry portrait of a 
serial killer and the cook the thief his wife amp her lover 
another miramax film have also been rated x last year the 
miramax film scandal was rated x but reduced to r 
after an orgy scene was recut 
