<TEXT>
mayor david dinkins on tuesday urged new yorkers 
to put aside racial antagonism and rededicate themselves to the 
values of justice opportunity and caring 
the public condemnation of racism the second in 12 days by the 
citys first black mayor follows a series of events that have 
heightened racial tensions in the city 
we will never get ahead if we are fighting each other for 
crumbs falling from the table of opportunity dinkins told a 
rally of 6000 
the powerless are trying to prove their power by hurting those 
who are just as powerless it must stop and it must stop now 
the most recent irritant to race relations was a pair of 
verdicts in the socalled bensonhurst case the killing of a black 
teenager by a mob of white youths 
one white teenager was convicted of killing a black youth 
during a gang attack in a predominantly white section of brooklyn 
in august a codefendant was acquitted of murder in the case but 
convicted of lesser charges 
a black boycott of a koreanamerican owned grocery store in 
brooklyn and a speech by a city university professor who espouses 
white supremacy also have brought recent frontpage headlines 
dinkins in announcing the citysponsored unity rally on monday 
said a silent majority needed to be heard above the voices of 
some activists who have been fueling instead of soothing tensions 
wherever you come from or whats been done to you you have no 
