democrats and 20 republicans who were elected with 55 percent or 
less of the vote in 1988 
democrats for example hope to oust rep denny smith rore 
who won reelection by just 707 votes last time is on the hit list 
of a national abortionrights group and has become enmeshed in the 
savings and loan problems 
republicans see an opportunity to oust some potentially 
vulnerable democrats but also must defend the seats vacated by 
their senate candidatesmost of their best opportunities are for 
vacant democratic seats 
their other targets include three north carolina democrats whose 
districts always produce squeakers 
the pay raise congress voted itself late last year could emerge 
as an issue for challengers even though republican and democratic 
leaders agreed to a nonaggression pact to win its passage 
