<TEXT>
one of the nations top cops reuben m 
greenberg is on the most wanted list of two historic southern 
port cities eager to keep him fighting crime on their streets 
the innovative officer is the onceandfuture police chief of 
charleston sc hes also midway through a sixmonth contract as 
public safety director in this bustling coastal city 
charleston expects him back in july mobiles leaders want him 
to stay 
people have got to stop zeroing in on me as the magic man 
said greenberg the author of lets take back our streets 
which details the law enforcement philosophy that has made him so 
popular on the lecture circuit 
his methods have worked like magic in charleston the murder 
rate is half what it was when he arrived in 1982 the overall crime 
rate has dropped more than 35 percent 
will his methods work in mobile a city with 2 times as many 
people and almost six times as much crime as charleston thats 
what greenberg is here to find out if his streetlevel assault is 
effective here it might work in new york or los angeles too 
greenberg does it by putting cops where the crime is in 
housing projects on street corners in front of crack houses and 
outside hotels where prostitutes take their customers 
he works to win the trust and cooperation of innercity 
residents who have lost faith in the system and have come to expect 
crime as part of their daily lives 
theyve given up whole sections of the city to the criminal 
