windows a type of program called a graphical user interface 
shields users from these commands by replacing them with onscreen 
pictures called icons and a mouse 
for example instead of having to type a command telling the 
computer to print a file windows provides a representation of a 
printer the user moves the cursor on the screen to the printer and 
pushes a button on the mouse to print the file 
