sock shop international plc will close 58 stores 
more than half its british outlets to try to save the business 
its administrators announced tuesday 
the company closed its 17 us stores in december 
the closure of 58 british stores out of 109 will mean 150 job 
losses the administrators said 
it has been a tough time for the employees of sock shop 
said administrator peter dubuisson 
i believe the steps we are now taking to rationalize the 
company will improve its profitability and reward everyones 
efforts to save sock shop he said 
dubuisson and phillip sykes accountants with the firm bdo 
binder hamlyn were called in three months ago last week a court 
gave them another three months to find a solution to propose to the 
companys creditors 
the administrators are looking for new investors to bail out the 
company which was founded in 1982 by a former typist sophie 
mirman and her husband richard ross 
the company has blamed its problems on last years hot summer 
and transport strikes which discouraged sales many sock shops are 
at train and subway stations 
