the soviet union could become the hottest growth 
market of the 21st century but serious impediments remain for 
exporters and investors us officials told hundreds of american 
and soviet business leaders tuesday 
the leaders of the usussr trade and economic council 
spoke optimistically at their 13th annual meeting that political 
barriers to better business relations between the two nations 
finally were being swept away 
however us ambassador jack matlock said the kremlins 
economic embargo of lithuania will make it difficult to get the 
us congress to approve a bilateral commercial agreement 
the failing soviet economy and mikhail s gorbachevs plans to 
introduce desperately needed market reforms kept surfacing at the 
session 
we understand that political freedom must be accompanied by 
meat on the table said alaska gov steve cowper addressing the 
meeting on his states recent cooperation with the soviet union 
for perestroika to work the soviet economic system has to work 
