like number of soviets that gorbachev and other kremlin leaders 
have had the courage to face these facts and to begin a massive 
restructuring program in the soviet union to take it away from the 
policies that have brought it to the brink of economic ruin 
if democratization and a movement toward a market economy 
continues the ussr could certainly be the growth market of 
the 21st century he said 
but he said key obstacles remain the soviet ruble is not 
convertible and foreign enterprises have not been fully integrated 
into the economy 
the soviets still try to contain and control foreign investment 
as a compartmentalized part of the economy basic factors such as 
market information advertising the ability to hire and fire local 
staff and the ability to communicate with potential customers and 
partners are needed to overcome this obstacle duesterburg said 
