said tuesday they would merge their businesses in industrial rubber 
products called tpes 
the enterprise would combine monsantos technical manufacturing 
and marketing expertise with exxon chemicals expertise in 
olefinbased raw materials and fundamental polymer science the 
companies said in a joint statement 
the material known as thermoplastic elastomers or tpes is a 
rubberlike substance that unlike the conventional vulcanized 
rubber can be easily processed and recycled tpes are used in 
engineered industrial rubber and soft plastic applications in the 
automotive medical food electrical construction appliance and 
business machine industries 
monsanto spokesman carl moskowitz said no dollar value has yet 
been placed on the venture but he said sales are expected to top 
100 million in 1990 and he said he expected the 30 to 35 percent 
annual growth in tpes sales experienced by monsanto to continue 
with the new company 
