citicorps credit rating was lowered tuesday by 
another major debtrating service which based its decision on 
concerns about the quality of real estate and takeover loans at the 
nations largest bank 
moodys investors service inc said it downgraded a total of 
374 billion in debt of citicorp some of its subsidiaries and 
debt that it guarantees the announcement came nearly one month 
after rival standard amp poors corp took similar action 
both credit rating firms said they were largely concerned about 
the effects of escalating problem real estate loans particularly 
in commerical developments given what they called citicorps weak 
earnings position and low capital levels 
they also cited worries about citicorps large third world debt 
portfolio and loans to finance takeovers 
lower credit ratings for citicorp is regarded as general sign of 
weakness in the banking sector and makes it more expensive for the 
bank to borrow money 
last month citicorp reported a 56 percent drop in firstquarter 
earnings mainly because of domestic real estate loan difficulties 
in slumping regions that are expected to worsen this year 
although citicorps real estate portfolio is geographically 
diverse and its underwriting standards appear to be sound moodys 
believes that citicorp is vulnerable to the deteriorating national 
real estate market moodys said in a statement 
a number of major banking institutions have seen their debt 
ratings lowered recently by moodys and sampp because of similar 
problems 
citicorp said it was disappointed by moodys action but added 
that it didnt expect the downgradings to significantly increase 
overall funding costs 
in a statement citicorp said it was confident the strength of 
its core businesses and wellpositioned global franchises will 
continue to provide excellent returns and growth 
although citicorps credit remains investmentgrade quality a 
lower rating heightens a banks borrowing costs by prompting 
investors to demand higher interest to compensate for increased 
risk the ratings have no effect on customer deposits 
the downgradings by moodys included citicorps senior debt to 
singleathree from singleaone commercial paper to primetwo 
from primeone and citibanks senior debt to singleaone from 
doubleatwo 
in additon it said it lowered about 62 billion in structured 
debt guaranteed by citicorp and citibank letters of credit 
