was originally filed by a former northrop employee under the 
federal false claims act 
the justice department intervened in the case and took over the 
litigation after apparently deciding not to file criminal charges 
as part of a deal with northrop last february 
under that deal northrop pleaded guilty to 34 criminal fraud 
counts and agreed to pay a 17 million fine for alleged 
falsification of tests on a stabilization control for the marine 
av8b harrier jet fighter and for the mx missile guidance mechanism 
the justice department lawsuit claimed northrop failed to 
disclose savings it made from a new manufacturing method for the 
fa18 parts 
the parts are made from composite materials and formed in a 
process that requires high pressure heat and vacuum 
the original suit was filed in 1987 by former northrop contract 
and pricing division manager eldon l janssen who claimed he 
learned of the alleged deceitful pricing in the course of his 
duties 
